@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "LineBloks" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries are
needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 4
colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any tile (except an 'Unclickable' tile) on the board,
this will rotate all 8 tiles surrounding it by one position in a clockwise
manner. If you click on a border tile, the tiles located at the other edge
of the board will rotate with the other tiles located around the tile you
clicked on. Note that when you click on 'Bomb' or 'Lightning' tiles, the
neighbouring tiles do not rotate.

  When you move tiles around, if a row or column of 8 tiles of the same
pattern is not formed, a new tile is added to the board. Be careful not to
let the board fill up completely because when that happens, the game is
over.

  When you complete a row or column with tiles of the same pattern, those
tiles are removed from the board and you get points depending on the
number of columns or rows you have made, 1 row or column of tiles of the
same pattern will give you 10 points, 2 rows or columns give 100 points,
3 rows or columns give 1000 points and so on...

  As you progress in the game, new tiles with different patterns are added
to the game board as well as the following tiles:

 -Bombs:             A Bomb (indicated by an 'explosion' icon) will
                     eliminate any tile that is located next to it,
                     either horizontally, vertically or diagonally.
                     Any tile removed will give you 1 point.

 -Unclickable Tiles: An Unclickable tile (indicated by a tile that is
                     'pressed down') is just that: unclickable, what this
                     means is that even if you click on it, nothing will
                     happen. The tiles surrounding it will not move. The
                     tile itself can move everywhere you like by clicking
                     on a neighbouring tile (unless of course if that
                     neighbouring tile is also unclickable).

 -Lightning Tiles:   A Lightning tile (indicated by an 'electric flash'
                     icon), when clicked on, will generate lightning
                     bolts horizontally and vertically, eliminating any
                     tiles that are located in their paths. Each tile
                     eliminated will give you 1 point.

 -Blocks:            Blocks do not serve any purpose other than being
                     there when you don't need them. They can be moved
                     anywhere you like.

  Continue the game until the board gets completely full or empty, in both
cases the game ends. If the board gets emptied, your final score will be
doubled.

  The game has a 'Top-10' that records the best score in the game,
unfortunately, it doesn't save the scores on disk (maybe in a future
release of the game...)

  Have fun!


OPTIONS

  2 buttons are shown in the game window:

 -About:  Displays the informations about the game.
 -Top 10: Displays the current best scores.

 Also there's a pull-down menu containing the following items:

 -About:        Displays the informations about the game.
 -Reset Top 10: Resets all the Top 10 scores to zero. 
 -Quit:         Quits the game (you can also use the
                Right-Amiga + "Q" keyboard equivalent).

@endnode

